  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Season your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723638626333-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723638626333-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723638626333-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723638626333-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1723638626333-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the<strong> seasoned chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-high, add 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>to the pan and cover with a lid</p><p>Cook for a further 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723638629149-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723638629149-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723638629149-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723638629149-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1723638629149-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong>, then top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into matchsticks</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>pho broth paste </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[800ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>pho stock</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
