            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a bowl and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside for 12-15 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, drain the noodles and set aside</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723638635302-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723638635302-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723638635302-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723638635302-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1723638635302-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>While the onion is cooking, shred the chicken apart using two forks - this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Set the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> aside for later</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1723638638848-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1723638638848-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1723638638848-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1723638638848-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1723638638848-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Strip most of your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, leave some on the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1723638642041-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1723638642041-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1723638642041-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1723638642041-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1723638642041-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>to the pan with the <strong>pho stock</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> fish sauce </strong>and<strong> pulled chicken</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 1-2 min or until the noodles are completely tender</p><p>Once tender, remove the pan from the heat and add the juice of <strong>half </strong>your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime[s] </strong>– this is your <strong>fragrant pho with shredded chicken</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime[s] </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1723638645062-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1723638645062-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1723638645062-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1723638645062-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1723638645062-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fragrant pho with shredded chicken</strong> topped with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>,<strong> mint leaves </strong>and <strong>mint</strong> <strong>stems</strong> and the <strong>carrot matchsticks</strong></p><p>Drizzle over your<strong> sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> </strong>garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
